  "doc": {
    "intent": "Bake photoreal bezel art by rendering Duimon Mega Bezel presets headlessly (librashader, Metal) and detecting exact screen holes with color-keyed probe cards. The baked PNG ships as the static bezel; holes are measured, never hand-tuned.",
    "probe": "Screen 1 renders solid magenta, screen 2 solid cyan; threshold bounding boxes give hole fractions in the same render that produces the art, so geometry is consistent by construction.",
    "day_variants": "Day ([Guest]/[LCD-GRID] without [Night]) keeps shell detail legible next to the pure-black bezel-off mode.",
    "flip": "Duimon 3DS presets set HSM_FLIP_VIEWPORT_VERTICAL=1 to compensate for citra-libretro's upside-down FBO output; azahar and the semu tap render upright, so n3ds bakes force it off (the art rendered upside down otherwise)."
  },
